                     <interp inst="t18280911-339-defend1841" type="age" value="29"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t18280911-339-off1741" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-339-off1741" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-339-off1741" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18280911-339-cd1742" type="crimeDate">19th of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-339-off1741 t18280911-339-cd1742"></join>, 1 truck, value 50s.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               <persName id="t18280911-339-victim1842" type="victimName">
                  John 
                  Hall
               <interp inst="t18280911-339-victim1842" type="surname" value="Hall"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-339-victim1842" type="given" value="John"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-339-victim1842" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-339-off1741 t18280911-339-victim1842"></join>
                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>JOHN HALL. I am a <rs id="t18280911-339-viclabel1743" type="occupation">wheel-right</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-339-victim1842 t18280911-339-viclabel1743"></join>. On the 18th of July, I let a truck to the prisoner, about half-past two o'clock - I heard no more of it till the next day; he said I had seen him before, but I could not recollect him; the next day I heard there was a truck stopped; I went and found it was mine - part of it was gone then.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did I borrow it of you or steal it? A. You borrowed it, and said you lived in Bunhill-row; he left 1s., and was to pay 3d. an hour for it - it was worth about 50s.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-339-person1843">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SMITH
               <interp inst="t18280911-339-person1843" type="surname" value="SMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-339-person1843" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-339-person1843" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner came to me, on the 19th of July, about three or four o'clock in the afternoon; he brought two trucks - one was broken and was on the top of the other; he offered that part of a truck, which was claimed by the prosecutor, for 10s.; he left it with me about two hours - the prosecutor claimed it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-339-person1844">
                  JOHN 
                  TWEEDY
               <interp inst="t18280911-339-person1844" type="surname" value="TWEEDY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-339-person1844" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-339-person1844" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I went and got the truck, and took the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I borrowed the truck for my own use, as I am in the habit of doing work for myself; I sent it home by my labourer, and till the next morning I did not know whether it was gone home safe - I came home from my work; he had sent word that he had given a boy 2d., and he had left the truck at such a place - I went and took it to Smith's to ask what it would cost to make it good, as I was in a very awkward predicament; I was going back and was taken.</p>
               <p>WILLIAM SMITH re-examined. Q. Did he bring it to sell or to mend? A. To sell.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280911-339-verdict1744" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-339-verdict1744" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 29.</p>
               <p>
